      <h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">Missed or partial payment</h1>

      <p class="govuk-body">A payment is missed when the receiving parent has:</p>
      <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
            <li>not received any payment 5 days after the date detailed on the payment plan. It can take up to 5 days for a payment to reach the receiving parentâ€™s account</li>
            <li>received less than 90% of the amount detailed on the payment plan</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="govuk-body">Find out <a class="govuk-link" href="#">what we can do to enforce the collection of unpaid child maintenance (opens in a new tab)</a>.</p>

      <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Collect and Pay service</h2>
      <p class="govuk-body">We know when a payment is missed or not paid in full. We will take the appropriate action to recover the payment.</p>

      <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Direct Pay service</h2>
      <p class="govuk-body">Contact the other parent if a payment is missed or not paid in full, it's the quickest way to sort it out. If this is not possible, the receiving parent needs to ask us to take action.<br><br>This could result in you having to use our Collect and Pay service and pay collection fees.</p>
